DURBAN - IFP leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi says his party is the strongest it's been in six years and he s ready to step down as a result.He described the Nquthu Municipality win as one of the IFP's biggest victories.Buthelezi, who founded the IFP in 1975, spoke to eNCA in an exclusive interview.UPDATE: IFP claims outright majority in NquthuHe s led the Inkatha Freedom Party through many victories and defeats since its inception in 1975, but Nquthu has given him reason to smile. The IFP leader is confident the party has a strong succession plan, and promises to make waves come 2019.* Watch the full video report by Thuba Vilane in the gallery above.eNCA